    "what_description": "Valeriana officinalis is a perennial herbaceous plant that belongs to the family Valerianaceae. It is native to Europe and Asia, but has been naturalized in North America. The plant grows to a height of 2-3 meters, with a branching stem and dark green, opposite, palmately divided leaves that are 5-10 cm long. The flowers are small, white or pink, and are arranged in a spike-like inflorescence. The root and rhizome of Valeriana officinalis contain valepotriates and other iridoid glycosides, which are responsible for its medicinal properties.",
