    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Valeriana officinalis are sedative, with its bioactive compounds, such as isovaleric acid and valerenic acid, contributing to the reduction of anxiety and stress in individuals. The plant's antispasmodic properties are attributed to the presence of valepotriates, which help to relax smooth muscles and alleviate muscle cramps and spasms. Additionally, Valeriana officinalis exhibits antioxidant properties due to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic compounds, which protect against oxidative stress and cellular damage. Its anti-inflammatory properties, mediated by valerenic acid and other bioactive compounds, may help to reduce inflammation and alleviate symptoms associated with conditions such as arthritis. Furthermore, the plant's anxiolytic effects, attributed to the presence of isovaleric acid and other bioactive compounds, have been shown to reduce anxiety and stress in individuals.",
