    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Valeriana officinalis are valerenic acid, valeranone, valerenal, valeranone acetate, and valerenol. These constituents have been identified as the primary active compounds responsible for the sedative and anxiolytic properties of the plant. Valerenic acid has been shown to modulate GABA receptors, promoting relaxation and reducing anxiety levels. Valeranone, valerenal, and valeranone acetate have been found to possess sedative and hypnotic properties, while valerenol has been demonstrated to have anxiolytic and muscle relaxant effects, contributing to the overall therapeutic benefits of Valeriana officinalis. The combination of these constituents in the plant results in its well-documented ability to alleviate insomnia, restlessness, and anxiety disorders.",
