    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Valeriana officinalis include valerian tincture, a concentrated liquid extract typically standardized to contain 0.8-1.2% valerenic acid and 0.2-0.5% isovaleric acid; valerian tea, a dried root infusion often steeped for 5-10 minutes to release its bioactive compounds; valerian capsules, filled with dried and powdered root, commonly containing 250-500mg of valerian extract per serving; valerian infusion, a cold-water extraction method that preserves the delicate constituents of the root, often used in traditional herbal medicine; and valerian oil, a solvent-based extract that may contain up to 20% valerenic acid, used in aromatherapy and topical applications.",
