    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Valeriana officinalis improperly include experiencing sedation, which may lead to impaired cognitive function and motor skills, as well as increased risk of falls and accidents. Experiencing dizziness is another potential side effect, particularly when consuming large doses or combining with other substances that can impair balance and equilibrium. Moreover, Valeriana officinalis can cause respiratory depression, a serious and potentially life-threatening condition characterized by slowed breathing rates, especially in individuals with pre-existing respiratory conditions or those who are taking other central nervous system depressants. Interacting with sedatives, such as benzodiazepines or barbiturates, can also exacerbate the sedative effects of Valeriana officinalis, leading to increased risk of respiratory depression and other adverse effects. These side effects occur because Valeriana officinalis contains valerenic acid, which can enhance the activity of GABA receptors in the brain, leading to sedative and hypnotic effects."
